INDIANAPOLIS - Veteran Simone Biles is good to go for a third straight world title, while a Minnesota kid will try to make her own splash on the international stage. 
Biles, an18-year-old from Spring, Texas, will lead the U.S. women's gymnastics team at the world championships in Glasgow, Scotland, this month. 
Defending Olympic all-around champion Gabrielle Douglas and three-time Olympic gold medalist Aly Raisman will be joined by Maggie Nichols of Little Canada to try and extend the Americans' dominance. The U.S. won its second team Olympic gold in London three years ago and easily captured the world title in China last fall. 
Madison Kocian, Brenna Dowell and MyKayla Skinner also made the team, though one athlete will be named an alternate before the competition begins Oct. 23. 
Biles, Kocian and Skinner were part of last year's world championship team. Read or Share this story: http://www.kare11.com/story/sports/2015/10/09/mn-gymnast-makes-us-womens-world-roster/73668950/ TOP VIDEOS
